<section id="body">
	<img class="rightFloat" src="../media/WB_WR8s.jpg" mode="1" id="1001"  /><img class="leftFloat" src="../media/WB_WR8.jpg" mode="16" id="1003"  /><br/><ol id="questionList"></ol>
</section>
<section id="fb1">
	<p align="left"><b>is used -> </b><font color="#0000ff"><b>uses</b><b>:</b> 'the Hong Kong Post Office' is the subject of this verb in active voice.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb2">
	<p align="left"><b>are involved -> </b><font color="#0000ff"><b>involve</b><b>:</b> 'The first stages' is the subject of this verb in active voice.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb3">
	<p align="left"><b>invited -> </b><font color="#0000ff"><b>invited</b><b>:</b> Passive is needed here.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb4">
	<p align="left"><b>simultaneously -> </b><font color="#0000ff"><b>subsequently</b><b>:</b> 'simultaneously' means 'at the same time' and 'subsequently' means 'afterwards'.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb5">
	<p align="left"><b>Prior to this -> </b><font color="#0000ff"><b>At this stage</b><b>:</b> 'Prior to this' means 'before'.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb6">
	<p align="left"><b>or -> </b><font color="#0000ff"><b>either</b><b>:</b> 'Either' introduces the first alternative.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb7">
	<p align="left"><b>In case -> </b><font color="#0000ff"><b>If</b><b>:</b> 'In case' does not have exactly the same meaning as 'if'.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb8">
	<p align="left"><b>commissioned -> </b><font color="#0000ff"><b>be commissioned</b><b>:</b> This verb is in passive voice in the future form, 'will be + past participle'. </font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb9">
	<p align="left"><b>choose -> </b><font color="#0000ff"><b>be chosen</b><b>:</b> This verb is in passive voice in the future form, 'will be + past participle'.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb10">
	<p align="left"><b>Before -> </b><font color="#0000ff"><b>Once</b><b>:</b> 'Once' here means 'as soon as'.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb11">
	<p align="left"><b>be chosen -> </b><font color="#0000ff"><b>choose</b><b>:</b> This verb is in passive voice in the future form, 'will be + past participle'.</font></p><p align="left"></p>
</section>
<section id="fb12">
	<p align="left"><b>sending -> </b><font color="#0000ff"><b>sent</b><b>:</b> The 'is' here is part of the passive verb. Present continuous is not appropriate here.</font></p>
</section>
